==English==
===Adjective===
'''cretic'''

#Referring to a [[metrical]] pattern of [[poetry]] where each [[foot]] is composed of 3 [[syllable]]s, the first and third of which are stressed and the second is unstressed.  This pattern is very rare in English poetry.
#:Example: In Shakespeare's A Midsummer Night's Dream the fairy speaks in '''cretic''' [[dimeter]] beginning: "Over hill, Over Dale." (Thus the line has six syllables and naturally is spoken as "OV-er HILL/OV-er DALE.")

